# Community Detection in Social Networks: A Comparative Study

## ğŸ“Œ Overview

This project focuses on **community detection** in social networks using various graph mining algorithms. The primary goal is to compare the performance and results of different community detection techniques on a real-world social graphâ€”the **Facebook combined ego-network dataset** from Stanford SNAP.

By analyzing centrality measures and applying community detection algorithms, this project aims to uncover the underlying structure of the network, identify key influencers, and evaluate how different algorithms partition the graph into meaningful communities.

